Denote by $h$ the height trapezoid $PQRS$


[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);
pair P, Q, R, S, A, M, N;
P = (1,4);
Q = (7,4);
R = (12,0);
S = (0,0);
A = intersectionpoint(Q--R,S--P);
M = (Q + R)/2;
N = (P + S)/2;
draw(P--Q--R--S--cycle);
draw(S--P);
label("$S$", S, SW);
label("$P$", P, NW);
label("$Q$", Q, NE);
label("$R$", R, SE);
label("$A$",(A + S)/2,S);
label("$M$",M,N);
label("$N$",N,N);
[/asy]
PQRS is trapezoid with height $h$.
The bases are length P=1 unit and length $Q=7$ units.


